<div style="background-color: #24242458; border-left: 5px solid #565656; border-right: 5px solid #565656; padding: 5px 3px; margin: 0.3em; text-align:left; font-size:25px;">  ✦ '''DESCRIPTION'''</div>
{{Blurimage|width=400px|align=right|file=Auroracorealiss1.jpg|caption=The most well-known photograph of Level 500.<br> - KhE = <span style="color:rgba(237, 255, 155, 1)">34RY</span> -}}
{{Blurimage|width=400px|align=right|file=Gaysky.jpg|caption=A photograph of Level 500, focusing on the trails.<br> - KhE = <span style="color:rgba(255, 233, 155, 1)">42RY</span> -}}
{{Blurimage|width=400px|align=right|file=Shrooms.jpg|caption=Image taken directly beneath the core via drone.<br> - KhE = <span style="color:rgba(190, 58, 58, 1)">612RY</span> -}}
Dominated by prismatic flares of light decorating the skies, '''Level 500''' is an amalgamation of rural residential areas darkened into a silhouetted shade. Roads, bearing signs of dilapidation and ruggedness, closely resemble trails in composition and proportions. Small trees, moss, and thickets of knee-height shrubbery comprise much of the level's natural areas. The scant traces of artificial structures primarily consist of small housing units - alongside those of miscellaneous purposes such as electrical boxes and non-functional street lamps. Open fields, if present in the slightest, typically possess barren surfaces with sparse spreads of lichen and weeds scattered across. Despite the lack of rainfall in '''Level 500''' (constantly remaining at a clear and non-humid state), all natural surfaces retain a light soak of fresh precipitation.

Aside from the aurora flares, only one natural light source is present in '''Level 500'''; that being a false celestial body referred to as the "core". Exhibiting faint layered rings of light to the viewer regardless of the angle, the core's location can be identified by the preference of violet hues among the aurora. The core is situated in a fixed area roughly 30 kilometers above ground as calculated from angular measurements, with the atmosphere of '''Level 500''' being nearly invisible. The environment's appearance closer to the vicinity of the core is noticeably more lustrous due to the higher levels of a special form of energy within such area.

The core in '''Level 500's''' skies is known to emit a special form of radiative wave known as "[[Object 499|Kharthiact (Object 499)]]" by physicists in the Backrooms. One of the most notable effects of Kharthic Energy is its ability to produce and refract light, with immense efficiency; in '''Level 500's''' case, causing the prismatic aurora effect in its sky. When objects are exposed to Kharthiact over prolonged periods of time, they will gradually develop more lustrous surfaces as well as having partially faded coloration.

Human exposure to high levels of Kharthic Energy tends to cause heightened anxiety, paranoia, and tension in the individual's mind. While the exact reasons behind why are unknown, these symptoms link to a considerable increase in adrenaline production alongside random neuron firings in the occipital and parietal lobe of the afflicted individual. These can cause extreme levels of stress, disorientation, and severe triggers in the fight-or-flight response. In most locations of '''Level 500,''' one will experience moderately negative symptoms regarding mental stress and anxiety. This depends on one's relative distance to the core, however; as one moves closer towards the core, they will be exposed to higher levels of Kharthiact.

Kharthiact is measured in RY (Reyennes), named after Swedish physicist Fredrik Reyenne who was the first to document and record his observations regarding Kharthic Energy. [[The Frontrooms]] is the only known example of a location possessing an absolute zero of Kharthic Energy; measured at 0RY. Most levels hover in the range of 2-3RY, while the average location in '''Level 500''' possesses 40RY. A lethal dose of Kharthiact depends on the individual, though exposure to ~550RY for approximately 60 seconds may be considered fatal for most.

